page.title: 04KINGSEEL COPSE
page.content: MR HARDING THE OWNER HAD KINDLY GIVEN US PERMISSION TO ENTER HIS COPSE. IT IS SO RAMPANT WITH TREES, CLIMBERS, FLOWERS AND STINGING NETTLES, THAT WE DECIDED TO STAY OUTSIDE. WE WALKED AROUND THE EDGE & RECOGNISED OAK, ASH, HOLLY, DOGWOOD, HAZEL, HAWTHORN & THE WAYFARING TREE. SCRAMBLING UP & OVER THE TREES WERE BLACKBERRIES, DOG ROSE, HONEY-SUCKLE, WILD CLEMATIS & IVY. THE TREES WERE MOSTLY SELF SOWN, CLOSE TOGETHER & FIGHTING FOR LIGHT. BROKEN BRANCHES WERE LEFT LYING. THROUGH ONE GAP WE SAW AN AMAZING SIGHT. TREES OF DIFFERING HEIGHTS, COVERED WITH CREEPERS & THE BLOOM OF THE WAYFARER TREE. ALL APPEARING AS SOLID AS A HILLSIDE STARRED WITH FLOWERS.
